HEADWORD: Falsely
<hw>False"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a false manner;
erroneously; not truly; perfidiously or treacherously.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧O
<xex>falsely</xex>, <xex>falsely</xex> murdered.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Oppositions of science, <qex>falsely</qex> so called.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Tim. vi. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Will ye steal, murder . . . and swear <qex>falsely</qex> ?</q>
